b Emirates visited the team of the first football team Palace Museum fort located in the capital Abu Dhabi<br><br>The Director General of the club, Mohammed Suhail Al-Kathiri, Chairman of the Community Initiatives and the Technical Director of Heavenly Winfried Schaefer, along with his technical, administrative and medical staff and all the first team players, were present.<br><br>The visit included all the parts and facilities of the museum where the mission was received warmly and generously by the officials in charge of the museum and was introduced to all the contents of the palace of archaeological treasures and various facilities during a tour that lasted more than an hour<br><br>Commenting on the visit, HE Mohammed Suhail Al-Katheri described the museum as precious to everyone and calls for pride and pride as it embraces many historical moments during the march of our beloved country in addition to opening its doors throughout the year to all visitors even from outside the country.<br><br>He added that there are directives from the club president HH Sheikh Saif bin Zayed Al Nahyan, Deputy Prime Minister and Minister of Interior, HH Sheikh Hamed bin Zayed Al Nahyan, vice president of the club and HH Sheikh Omar bin Zayed Al Nahyan, second vice president of the club. Bani Yas Club is a race in support of tourism, culture and national heritage and we as officials in the club are proud and proud to be here, especially as this museum means a lot to us.<br><br>Finally, the players and all members of the mission expressed their happiness to learn about the wings of this historic landmark and unique architectural style, stressing the club\'s usual role in creating a family atmosphere within the team with more harmony between all elements of the team in particular and all members of the club in general.','cb15175bc8ccb41512a60cf2140f0e66.jpg,028eab42ea1b6719fecf9f75bfd16c82.jpg,05da07ba2dd5c51e80bd33d934c476b7.jpg,40fef3ed1c56ddac4b3fa92c9c636345.jpg,43336a0f93efbc1fa